1
00:00:39,367 --> 00:00:40,033
<i> All right, Mom.</i>

2
00:00:40,167 --> 00:00:41,100
<i> Just make a choice.</i>

3
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:44,400
<i>Manuel and Jessica,
or me and Jeff?</i>

4
00:00:44,533 --> 00:00:46,133
<i> Please, stay here with us.</i>

5
00:00:46,267 --> 00:00:47,367
<i> What you want is impossible.</i>

6
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:49,733
<i>If you make them leave,
I'm going with them.</i>

7
00:00:49,867 --> 00:00:50,967
<i>I don't think it
will help you.</i>

8
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:52,500
<i> Felma made up her mind.</i>

9
00:00:52,633 --> 00:00:53,800
<i> We can no longer change that.</i>

10
00:00:53,933 --> 00:00:56,067
<i>It's just sad
that she can't accept me</i>

11
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:58,367
<i> the way Coleen accepts me.</i>

12
00:00:58,500 --> 00:00:59,967
<i>I've been patient with you
for a long time.</i>

13
00:01:00,100 --> 00:01:01,500
<i> But you're going too far.</i>

14
00:01:01,633 --> 00:01:02,933
<i> You want to leave, don't you?</i>

15
00:01:03,067 --> 00:01:04,533
<i>Fine. I'll even walk you out
myself!</i>

16
00:01:04,667 --> 00:01:05,767
<i>You're really
kicking Andrea out?</i>

17
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:06,933
<i> We've come to this point?</i>

18
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:09,133
<i>You're that desperate
to be with your ex?</i>

19
00:01:09,267 --> 00:01:13,400
<i>If you refuse to obey,
if you won't follow me...</i>

20
00:01:14,167 --> 00:01:14,867
<i> Fine!</i>

21
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:16,667
<i> Go ahead!</i>

22
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:21,167
<i>Anyone who wants to leave
is welcome to do so now!</i>

23
00:01:22,567 --> 00:01:24,067
<i> Felma, that's enough.</i>

24
00:01:28,533 --> 00:01:30,433
Don't let it come to this.

25
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:33,867
If anyone's leaving,
it should be me.

26
00:01:35,233 --> 00:01:36,100
Nothing's changing
with the plan.

27
00:01:36,233 --> 00:01:37,433
Jessica and I are leaving.

28
00:01:37,567 --> 00:01:41,067
And then what? You expect us
to believe what you're saying?

29
00:01:41,233 --> 00:01:42,600
Son, it's the truth.

30
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:45,667
I don't want to be a burden
to you anymore.

31
00:01:46,367 --> 00:01:49,200
I don't want to be the reason
your family falls apart.

32
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:51,800
Jeff...

33
00:01:53,033 --> 00:01:53,967
Andeng.

34
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:56,767
Please, I'm begging you.

35
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,433
Don't let your family
fall apart.

36
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:03,367
Don't leave your mom.

37
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:14,033
Andeng!

38
00:02:33,167 --> 00:02:34,433
Have you talked
to a lawyer yet?

39
00:02:34,567 --> 00:02:35,933
About the Family Code?

40
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:38,300
There's Atty. Buenafe.

41
00:02:38,767 --> 00:02:40,300
My friend recommended her.

42
00:02:40,433 --> 00:02:42,067
But turns out
she's already abroad.

43
00:02:43,433 --> 00:02:44,533
See? This is what I mean.

44
00:02:44,867 --> 00:02:46,967
You keep suggesting
I sue Manuel,

45
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,467
but you can't even
follow through.

46
00:02:49,233 --> 00:02:51,133
I am already looking
for a lawyer.

47
00:02:53,433 --> 00:02:54,733
You know, I was thinking...

48
00:02:55,667 --> 00:02:57,300
why don't you just
go back to Paz?

49
00:02:57,767 --> 00:02:59,567
Keep pretending
to be her client.

50
00:03:01,933 --> 00:03:03,400
After what she did to you?

51
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:04,533
No way.

52
00:03:04,933 --> 00:03:06,333
That girl might catch me.

53
00:03:06,467 --> 00:03:07,300
Hello?

54
00:03:07,433 --> 00:03:09,067
She might even mess up
my pretty face!

55
00:03:09,933 --> 00:03:10,733
Don't worry, I've got your back.

56
00:03:10,867 --> 00:03:11,967
She won't find out.

57
00:03:12,967 --> 00:03:15,633
Girl, our enemy is sharp.
She's no joke.

58
00:03:16,367 --> 00:03:18,467
What if Paz tells Felma?

59
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:19,633
I'm dead.

60
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,600
So she's going to drag me
through the mud

61
00:03:21,767 --> 00:03:23,000
like she did to you?

62
00:03:24,433 --> 00:03:25,567
Excuse me.

63
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:27,700
I would've gotten back at her
if we hadn't been stopped.

64
00:03:28,467 --> 00:03:31,433
Besides, you need
to return to Paz.

65
00:03:31,933 --> 00:03:33,433
We need to outsmart that woman,

66
00:03:33,567 --> 00:03:36,533
because I'm sure she knows
where my darn husband is.

67
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:05,367
Mom?

68
00:04:14,667 --> 00:04:16,867
Sorry for disrespecting you.

69
00:04:17,633 --> 00:04:19,933
I challenged you earlier...

70
00:04:20,933 --> 00:04:24,433
that I'd leave if I didn't get
what I wanted.

71
00:04:25,467 --> 00:04:26,733
I'm sorry, Mom.

72
00:04:44,267 --> 00:04:48,000
He lectures as if he's some
kind of a saint!

73
00:04:49,467 --> 00:04:51,300
And mom believes every word
like he's the greatest!

74
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:03,733
Does she really think I enjoy
talking back to her

75
00:05:04,867 --> 00:05:06,633
and to that so-called
father of Coleen?

76
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:10,500
I don't like getting
angry, Jeff.

77
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:13,867
I don't want to disrespect mom.

78
00:05:16,067 --> 00:05:17,933
But I honestly don't know
what to do anymore.

79
00:05:19,733 --> 00:05:21,033
Because it hurts.

80
00:05:21,967 --> 00:05:25,167
It really hurts
every time I see that man.

81
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:30,667
I get you.

82
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,767
I don't want to talk
back to mom, either.

83
00:05:36,267 --> 00:05:37,233
It's just frustrating

84
00:05:37,367 --> 00:05:38,933
because it feels like
they don't understand us.

85
00:05:40,633 --> 00:05:41,733
But what else can we do?

86
00:05:42,433 --> 00:05:44,433
She already got fooled
by that crippled guy.

87
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,033
Her and Coleen.

88
00:05:48,533 --> 00:05:52,067
Mom's siding with Jessica
and that man.

89
00:05:53,633 --> 00:05:54,767
This will all end
soon anyway, right?

90
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:55,933
They're leaving.

91
00:05:56,633 --> 00:05:58,333
Those two leaving?
Don't count on it.

92
00:05:58,567 --> 00:05:59,733
We should be the ones to leave.

93
00:06:00,867 --> 00:06:01,767
Where would we even go?

94
00:06:04,567 --> 00:06:05,667
Whatever happens, happens.

95
00:06:06,367 --> 00:06:07,700
We'll find somewhere to stay.

96
00:06:09,667 --> 00:06:12,367
You can stay with your
daughter and her mom, right?

97
00:06:13,067 --> 00:06:14,500
Andrea, it's not that simple.

98
00:06:15,533 --> 00:06:17,133
Just admit that you're a coward.

99
00:06:18,433 --> 00:06:20,433
You're used to always
depending on mom.

100
00:06:21,767 --> 00:06:22,733
I'm not a coward!

101
00:06:23,533 --> 00:06:25,900
Look, I'm just thinking
about what's best for us.

102
00:06:26,733 --> 00:06:29,667
You know, you're fearless
because you finished school.

103
00:06:30,133 --> 00:06:32,400
Even if you quit your job,
you'll find another one easily.

104
00:06:32,533 --> 00:06:34,633
If you had just taken your
studies seriously back then,

105
00:06:34,767 --> 00:06:36,133
you wouldn't be so insecure now!

106
00:06:36,267 --> 00:06:37,233
If you weren't such a brat,

107
00:06:37,367 --> 00:06:38,200
maybe we wouldn't be fighting
right now, right?

108
00:06:38,333 --> 00:06:39,233
Fine!

109
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:41,433
That makes me the bad one!

110
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,100
And you're the good child!

111
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:50,000
Are you crazy?

112
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:51,800
You're really leaving?

113
00:06:52,533 --> 00:06:53,333
No one's leaving.

114
00:06:53,467 --> 00:06:54,867
- Stop.
- What are you doing, Jeff?

115
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:57,067
If you're not coming with me,
just let me go.

116
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,400
I'm leaving!

117
00:06:58,533 --> 00:06:59,100
No one's leaving!

118
00:06:59,233 --> 00:07:00,033
Andrea, stop.

119
00:07:00,167 --> 00:07:01,000
- No one's leaving!
- What the hell!

120
00:07:03,633 --> 00:07:05,267
Just let me leave!

121
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:08,767
You leave!

122
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:11,033
- Go with your parents!
- We need to talk first.

123
00:07:11,167 --> 00:07:13,367
- Stay together. All of you!
- Andrea! Andrea!

124
00:07:30,900 --> 00:07:32,100
Jeff!

125
00:07:32,233 --> 00:07:33,100
Jeff!

126
00:07:33,233 --> 00:07:35,333
Sorry for bringing
dad and Jessica here.

127
00:07:35,467 --> 00:07:36,967
I already warned you it'll bring
us trouble, remember?

128
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:38,067
Did you listen?

129
00:07:38,733 --> 00:07:39,933
That's why I'm apologizing.

130
00:07:40,067 --> 00:07:41,333
What good is your apology?

131
00:07:42,167 --> 00:07:43,767
Mom is furious at us.

132
00:07:44,467 --> 00:07:47,800
Let her cool down first,
and then you apologize.

133
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:49,000
And then what?

134
00:07:49,900 --> 00:07:51,100
She's just going
to forgive us?

135
00:07:51,867 --> 00:07:53,967
And then your darn father
gets to stay here?

136
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:56,767
Come on, Coleen, try to
understand me and Andrea!

137
00:07:58,967 --> 00:08:00,000
You know, I wish I were
just a baby

138
00:08:00,133 --> 00:08:01,467
when your father left us.

139
00:08:02,733 --> 00:08:04,033
So I didn't have to feel
the pain of being abandoned

140
00:08:04,167 --> 00:08:05,100
by a dad.

141
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:23,033
Come in!

142
00:08:28,967 --> 00:08:30,533
I'm glad you came.

143
00:08:30,667 --> 00:08:32,567
I've been worried about you.

144
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,633
I'm okay.

145
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:39,200
I'm managing.

146
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:43,867
I apologize on behalf
of our children.

147
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,733
It's my fault they
ended up like this.

148
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:51,567
The wound I left
on them is deep.

149
00:08:54,267 --> 00:08:55,933
Time hasn't healed it.

150
00:08:57,700 --> 00:08:59,100
You hurt me, too.

151
00:09:00,567 --> 00:09:03,533
But I chose to heal.

152
00:09:05,633 --> 00:09:11,200
They could choose to heal, too,

153
00:09:12,433 --> 00:09:14,100
but they keep letting anger
control them.

154
00:09:15,667 --> 00:09:18,467
Manuel, I don't know what
to do with your kids anymore.

155
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:21,233
Felma, there's only one
solution.

156
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:23,467
Jessica and I need to leave.

157
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:24,867
You're not leaving.

158
00:09:25,367 --> 00:09:26,533
Stay here.

159
00:09:26,667 --> 00:09:29,400
Things will only get worse
if we don't leave.

160
00:09:30,167 --> 00:09:32,933
I don't want you to hate
each other for good.

161
00:09:33,467 --> 00:09:34,867
Coleen needs you.

162
00:09:35,967 --> 00:09:37,733
She needs a father.

163
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,167
Felma, I also need Coleen.

164
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:42,567
I also need Jeffrey and Andrea.

165
00:09:43,567 --> 00:09:44,700
But how?

166
00:09:44,833 --> 00:09:46,433
They just can't forgive me.

167
00:09:46,567 --> 00:09:48,167
That's why you shouldn't leave.

168
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:49,367
Stay here.

169
00:09:51,167 --> 00:09:53,267
Try to make it up to them.

170
00:09:54,233 --> 00:09:56,900
Maybe, if they see you're
sincere,

171
00:09:57,567 --> 00:09:59,267
they'll forgive you.

172
00:10:00,067 --> 00:10:01,667
That's all we have to hold onto.

173
00:10:02,133 --> 00:10:05,900
Yeah, but what if Hazel
tracks us down?

174
00:10:41,733 --> 00:10:43,300
What are you doing here?

175
00:10:44,267 --> 00:10:45,900
Looking for another fight?

176
00:10:46,367 --> 00:10:48,367
I just came here to apologize.

177
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:51,367
I'm the only one
trying to help you.

178
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:53,300
You ruined my plan.

179
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:56,933
Do you really think it was right
to rat me out to Felma?

180
00:10:57,733 --> 00:10:59,767
I didn't mean for that
to happen.

181
00:11:00,367 --> 00:11:01,200
Yeah, right.

182
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:03,133
You really deserve
a best actress award.

183
00:11:03,267 --> 00:11:05,367
You know, I'm not
falling for it anymore.

184
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:11,400
What did you expect to gain
by barging in on Felma?

185
00:11:11,533 --> 00:11:13,367
It only made her even
less likely to tell you

186
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:15,033
where your husband is.

187
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:19,833
So Felma knows where Manuel is?

188
00:11:19,967 --> 00:11:20,700
No.

189
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:21,933
She doesn't know.

190
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:23,433
And you definitely know.

191
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:24,833
No, I don't know.

192
00:11:25,367 --> 00:11:26,667
Liar.

193
00:11:27,133 --> 00:11:30,533
Hazel, can you please
leave their family alone?

194
00:11:30,667 --> 00:11:34,133
They're already fighting
because of your husband.

195
00:11:34,267 --> 00:11:36,433
For the sake of my godchildren,
I'm begging you.

196
00:11:36,567 --> 00:11:39,433
Stop messing with them.

197
00:11:39,567 --> 00:11:44,900
They don't even know how to get
along with your husband anymore!

198
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,033
To get along?

199
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:49,067
So I was right.

200
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:51,733
My husband and daughter
are at Felma's house.

201
00:11:51,867 --> 00:11:53,500
I didn't say anything like that!

202
00:11:59,233 --> 00:12:00,367
Felma!

203
00:12:01,467 --> 00:12:04,100
Oh my gosh! Andrea.

204
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:07,433
Jeff, are you really leaving?

205
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:11,067
Jeff, Andrea, don't go, please.

206
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,300
Don't!

207
00:12:12,433 --> 00:12:13,567
Jeff!

208
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:14,967
Andrea, please!

209
00:12:15,133 --> 00:12:16,433
- Andrea.
- Don't leave!

210
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:18,867
I'm sorry. Please forgive me.

211
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:19,800
Let go of me.

212
00:12:20,467 --> 00:12:23,100
What do you want me to do
so you can forgive me?

213
00:12:23,233 --> 00:12:25,533
For you to stay?

214
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,200
Kick your father out of here.

215
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:30,367
And your illegitimate
sister, too. Send her away.

216
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:35,500
You can't do that, can you?

217
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:37,467
Step aside.

218
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:40,700
Please, let's talk this through.

219
00:12:40,833 --> 00:12:42,100
Jeff!

220
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:45,333
Andrea, Jeff, please.

221
00:12:45,467 --> 00:12:47,467
Don't make it hard
for your sister.

222
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:49,700
Didang, can you please
stay out of it?

223
00:12:49,867 --> 00:12:51,133
Mom!

224
00:12:51,267 --> 00:12:53,833
- Jeff and Andrea are leaving!
- Quiet!

225
00:12:53,967 --> 00:12:55,133
Mom will hear you!

226
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:02,900
Mom, don't let them leave.

227
00:13:03,033 --> 00:13:04,733
Please stop them.

228
00:13:10,567 --> 00:13:13,933
Mom, please stop them
from leaving.

229
00:13:14,933 --> 00:13:15,933
That's what they want.

230
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:17,833
Let's just let them be.

231
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:19,867
Mom?

232
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:24,867
Why should we stop them if they
don't want to be with us, right?

233
00:13:29,067 --> 00:13:29,933
Let's go, Jeff.

234
00:13:31,667 --> 00:13:33,467
Andrea!

235
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:36,200
Andrea!

236
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:37,267
Andrea!

237
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:38,167
Stop.

238
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:41,267
- Jeff!
- You heard mom, right?

239
00:13:42,100 --> 00:13:44,533
Jeff!

240
00:13:45,167 --> 00:13:47,167
Andrea! Jeff!

241
00:13:52,500 --> 00:13:56,933
Mom, why did you let them leave?

242
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:01,833
What?

243
00:14:02,500 --> 00:14:04,133
Your husband's at her house?

244
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:06,500
So all this time,

245
00:14:06,633 --> 00:14:08,533
she's been pretending
she doesn't know anything?

246
00:14:09,267 --> 00:14:11,700
Friend, you've been played!

247
00:14:12,333 --> 00:14:14,000
Go ahead, rub it in.

248
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:19,433
I've always suspected
that Felma.

249
00:14:19,867 --> 00:14:21,300
But now, I've got proof.

250
00:14:21,867 --> 00:14:24,033
My darn husband can't escape me
this time.

251
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:26,467
Where is that Maximo anyway?

252
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,300
He's taking forever.

253
00:14:27,433 --> 00:14:28,467
Is he coming? Why?

254
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:30,600
Just leave it be.
Don't get involved.

255
00:14:30,733 --> 00:14:32,067
I just want to help!

256
00:14:32,567 --> 00:14:33,300
No, don't.

257
00:14:33,433 --> 00:14:35,633
Because you can't
be seen with me.

258
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,567
I need you more
at Felma's office.

259
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:39,133
You can gossip there.

260
00:14:40,933 --> 00:14:42,400
Classmate, I'm here!

261
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:44,200
Finally.

262
00:14:44,333 --> 00:14:45,267
You're late.

263
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:47,233
If only I had someone else
to ask for help.

264
00:14:47,667 --> 00:14:49,067
What exactly do
you want me to do?

265
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:54,533
Wow, you talk as if your
last plan worked.

266
00:14:55,067 --> 00:14:57,067
Just make sure you don't
get caught this time.

267
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,600
Is your phone camera any good?

268
00:15:00,167 --> 00:15:00,967
Of course.

269
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:02,033
Let me see it.

270
00:15:02,533 --> 00:15:03,633
Why do you ask?

271
00:15:08,467 --> 00:15:10,233
Make sure it's fully charged,
okay?

272
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,333
We've got someone to catch.

273
00:15:13,567 --> 00:15:14,400
Let's go.

274
00:15:14,867 --> 00:15:16,000
You take charge here, Alice.

275
00:15:18,867 --> 00:15:20,133
I'll keep you posted.

276
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:25,600
Why don't you just use your car?

277
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:27,533
That's mom's car.

278
00:15:27,933 --> 00:15:29,067
She might hold it against me.

279
00:15:32,467 --> 00:15:35,467
Oh, my<i> Sakay</i> car is
almost ready anyway.

280
00:15:36,233 --> 00:15:37,233
You know, I still don't get it.

281
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:38,867
Why did mom let us leave?

282
00:15:39,567 --> 00:15:40,333
I don't know, Jeff.

283
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:43,467
Let's just let it be.

284
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,367
Let's accept that...

285
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:47,667
this is how things are now.

286
00:15:48,433 --> 00:15:49,300
Where will you stay?

287
00:15:49,867 --> 00:15:51,167
With Auntie Paz.

288
00:15:51,667 --> 00:15:52,933
I told you, just come with me.

289
00:15:53,067 --> 00:15:54,433
Daisy would understand.

290
00:15:54,567 --> 00:15:57,233
It's as if her apartment
is huge enough for all of us.

291
00:15:58,233 --> 00:15:59,500
Here's my ride.

292
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,233
Andrea, call me, okay?

293
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,500
Keep me updated.

294
00:16:11,633 --> 00:16:12,867
About your plans in life.

295
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,000
Yes, Jeff.

296
00:16:14,133 --> 00:16:15,433
Don't worry.

297
00:16:15,567 --> 00:16:17,467
I'm no longer the
10-year-old kid with asthma.

298
00:16:24,367 --> 00:16:25,300
Bye.

299
00:16:27,667 --> 00:16:28,467
Take care.

300
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:31,633
Text and call me.

301
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:33,400
Call me right away, okay?

302
00:16:33,533 --> 00:16:34,967
I will!

303
00:17:08,667 --> 00:17:09,467
Felma.

304
00:17:11,267 --> 00:17:13,733
So Andrea and Jeffrey still went
through with leaving.

305
00:17:15,967 --> 00:17:17,000
I'm sorry.

306
00:17:17,767 --> 00:17:19,933
Looks like my advice
meant nothing to them.

307
00:17:21,533 --> 00:17:23,733
But really, who am I
for them to listen to?

308
00:17:23,867 --> 00:17:25,500
I was gone for so many years.

309
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:28,133
Maybe I'm partly to blame.

310
00:17:28,900 --> 00:17:31,967
I was full of anger back

311
00:17:34,033 --> 00:17:35,467
when I was trying to get back
on my feet.

312
00:17:36,033 --> 00:17:39,333
Perhaps because
of the resentment,

313
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,167
I've influenced them.

314
00:17:44,367 --> 00:17:46,333
So it's not easy
for them to forgive.

315
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:49,000
Don't blame yourself.

316
00:17:49,167 --> 00:17:50,833
You did so many things right.

317
00:17:51,533 --> 00:17:57,867
Do you think I was right
to let them leave, Manuel?

318
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:02,300
You've been making decisions
for our kids for many years.

319
00:18:02,767 --> 00:18:05,100
If you think this is
the best thing to do,

320
00:18:05,233 --> 00:18:07,500
the right way for them to learn,

321
00:18:08,267 --> 00:18:10,867
then who am I
to say you're wrong?

322
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:22,433
Sir.

323
00:18:22,567 --> 00:18:23,733
<i> Sakay</i> pick up, boss.

324
00:18:23,867 --> 00:18:27,867
I need to pick up a passenger
at Miss Felma Ruiz's house.

325
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:29,667
May I borrow your ID, please?

326
00:18:47,367 --> 00:18:51,500
Sir, just go straight and
turn right at the third corner.

327
00:18:51,633 --> 00:18:54,133
Miss Felma's house
is on the right.

328
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:55,400
- Thank you, boss.
- All right, take care.

329
00:19:01,867 --> 00:19:05,367
You'd better be ready for me,
Felma, you flirt.

330
00:19:19,567 --> 00:19:23,133
<i>All right!
My fellow loudmouths...</i>

331
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:24,600
Didang?

332
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:25,767
Ma'am?

333
00:19:25,900 --> 00:19:28,233
Is what we're going
to cook ready?

334
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,433
Oh, yes, Ma'am.

335
00:19:29,567 --> 00:19:30,333
The pan's hot.

336
00:19:30,467 --> 00:19:31,600
You can start sautéing.

337
00:19:34,267 --> 00:19:36,133
What are you watching?

338
00:19:36,267 --> 00:19:38,367
You seem a little distracted.

339
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:40,000
Oh, sorry, Ma'am...

340
00:19:40,133 --> 00:19:43,933
It's just that this is my
favorite vlogger on ViewTube.

341
00:19:44,067 --> 00:19:45,767
She exposes all the gossip!

342
00:19:45,900 --> 00:19:48,033
Look, Ma'am. Here, watch this.

343
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:49,233
Put that away for now.

344
00:19:49,367 --> 00:19:50,333
Come on, stop watching.

345
00:19:50,467 --> 00:19:52,400
- Yeah, let's start cooking.
- Let's cook.

346
00:19:52,533 --> 00:19:56,633
And I know we're
making afritada.

347
00:19:56,767 --> 00:19:58,667
But the one who loves it
the most isn't even here

348
00:19:58,800 --> 00:19:59,933
to eat it.

349
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:05,567
We can still cook it though...

350
00:20:06,267 --> 00:20:08,733
because it's Manuel's favorite.

351
00:20:13,233 --> 00:20:16,367
What I mean is,
he really is her father.

352
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:18,700
They have the same taste.

353
00:20:21,933 --> 00:20:22,900
Sorry, Ma'am.

354
00:20:23,033 --> 00:20:24,567
It slipped out.

355
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:28,133
There's nothing wrong
with talking about Manuel.

356
00:20:29,067 --> 00:20:32,967
In fact, it kind of feels like
a blessing in disguise

357
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:34,667
that Manuel is here.

358
00:20:35,267 --> 00:20:38,767
We've actually been able
to talk about the kids.

359
00:20:39,667 --> 00:20:41,467
So, it's okay to talk about him?

360
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:43,333
So, how did he court you?

361
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:47,967
Come on, Ma'am.

362
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:50,033
Answer it later.

363
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:52,367
Hello, friend?

364
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:53,367
Felma...

365
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:56,333
I don't even know
how to tell you this.

366
00:20:56,467 --> 00:20:58,200
What is it this time?

367
00:20:58,333 --> 00:21:01,933
Felma, that short little witch
outsmarted me!

368
00:21:02,067 --> 00:21:03,167
She totally got me.

369
00:21:03,300 --> 00:21:06,800
She figured out that Manuel's
staying with you.

370
00:21:06,933 --> 00:21:08,400
Seriously!

371
00:21:08,567 --> 00:21:10,067
<i> I'm sorry, I'm really sorry.</i>

372
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:11,267
Please forgive me.

373
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:13,600
Fine, when we see each other,
you can pull my hair,

374
00:21:13,733 --> 00:21:15,367
slap me, whatever you want.

375
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:18,333
But right now, I'm warning you.

376
00:21:19,167 --> 00:21:19,833
Okay.

377
00:21:26,667 --> 00:21:27,700
- Didang.
- Ma'am.

378
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:29,267
Call the guard.

379
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:34,500
Make sure that Hazel doesn't get
into our subdivision.

380
00:21:34,633 --> 00:21:36,200
Don't worry, Ma'am.
I've got it covered.

381
00:22:09,267 --> 00:22:11,100
Bro, I followed her.

382
00:22:11,233 --> 00:22:13,433
Bro, you actually went
through with the plan?

383
00:22:14,133 --> 00:22:15,300
<i> You're stalking Andrea?</i>

384
00:22:15,933 --> 00:22:17,433
I didn't mean to.

385
00:22:18,900 --> 00:22:20,633
I just wanted to visit her...

386
00:22:20,767 --> 00:22:23,367
but then I saw she
had bags with her.

387
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:25,000
<i> Looks like she's leaving.</i>

388
00:22:26,067 --> 00:22:29,100
I don't know why, but every time
I see her, she seems troubled.

389
00:22:30,367 --> 00:22:31,933
Maybe this is my chance to help.

390
00:22:32,667 --> 00:22:33,800
It's destiny, I swear.

391
00:22:34,233 --> 00:22:35,367
Destiny, my foot.

392
00:22:46,967 --> 00:22:48,467
She doesn't need me anymore.

393
00:22:49,300 --> 00:22:51,067
Looks like someone else
already helped her.

394
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,467
What a bummer.

395
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,433
So there's no such thing
as destiny.

396
00:22:53,567 --> 00:22:54,833
All right then.
Keep me updated, okay?

397
00:23:04,567 --> 00:23:05,333
So?

398
00:23:05,900 --> 00:23:06,667
Are you ready to record?

399
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:07,800
Yeah.

400
00:23:07,933 --> 00:23:10,500
Just remember, I should only be
seen from the back,

401
00:23:10,633 --> 00:23:12,233
like my hair, shoulder,
that kind of angle.

402
00:23:12,367 --> 00:23:13,833
And focus on Felma.

403
00:23:13,967 --> 00:23:14,900
I want her to be humiliated.

404
00:23:15,033 --> 00:23:16,767
- Okay, okay, rolling now.
- Okay?

405
00:23:16,900 --> 00:23:18,667
We're good? Rolling now?

406
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:19,900
Didang.

407
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:21,067
- Ma'am.
- Didang!

408
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,300
Are you still not done?

409
00:23:23,433 --> 00:23:25,833
Just finishing touches, Ma'am.

410
00:23:25,967 --> 00:23:27,067
You'll get to taste it soon.

411
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:29,567
Stop watching that already.

412
00:23:29,700 --> 00:23:30,633
Come on, Ma'am.

413
00:23:30,767 --> 00:23:31,633
Mom's right.

414
00:23:31,767 --> 00:23:32,667
I'm hungry.

415
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:33,933
Exactly. There,
it's almost done.

416
00:23:34,067 --> 00:23:35,700
Oh, it's ready!

417
00:23:40,833 --> 00:23:42,867
Felma!

418
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:43,767
I know you're in there!

419
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:45,533
Come out!

420
00:23:45,667 --> 00:23:46,633
That one's not calming down
at all.

421
00:23:46,767 --> 00:23:47,733
- So furious.
- Who's that?

422
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:51,167
I got it, Ma'am.

423
00:23:51,700 --> 00:23:52,333
Hey!

424
00:23:52,467 --> 00:23:54,200
What's going on? Wait a minute.

425
00:23:54,333 --> 00:23:56,967
What are you doing? Pressing
the doorbell like crazy.

426
00:23:57,767 --> 00:23:58,733
Who do you think you are?

427
00:23:59,167 --> 00:23:59,900
You've been at it
for a while now...

428
00:24:00,033 --> 00:24:00,967
Let Felma out.

429
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:01,967
= Hey! You can't!
- I know she's in there...

430
00:24:02,100 --> 00:24:04,167
Hey! You can't! You're a demon!
I know you!

431
00:24:04,300 --> 00:24:05,367
- And why do you have that?
- Move side.

432
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:07,900
That's not allowed!

433
00:24:08,033 --> 00:24:08,633
Felma!

434
00:24:08,767 --> 00:24:09,500
Hey! Hey!

435
00:24:09,633 --> 00:24:10,233
You witch!

436
00:24:10,367 --> 00:24:11,233
No! You can't!

437
00:24:11,367 --> 00:24:12,533
- You can't!
- Felma!

438
00:24:12,667 --> 00:24:13,733
- You can't go in there!
- This is our house!

439
00:24:13,867 --> 00:24:14,700
- You can't get in!
- She told you to move!

440
00:24:14,833 --> 00:24:15,567
Take care of her!

441
00:24:15,967 --> 00:24:17,033
Hey! Felma!

442
00:24:17,167 --> 00:24:18,933
Felma, bring out my husband
and my child!

443
00:24:19,067 --> 00:24:20,967
- My employer's not here!
- What's going on here?

444
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:22,367
<i> Why are you inside my house?</i>

445
00:24:22,500 --> 00:24:23,833
<i>What do you mean she's not here?
Look!</i>

446
00:24:23,967 --> 00:24:25,733
<i>So? Where are my husband
and my child?</i>

447
00:24:25,867 --> 00:24:26,833
Go ahead, film it, film it!

448
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:30,600
<i> Who are you?</i>

449
00:24:30,733 --> 00:24:31,733
<i> Jeffrey!</i>

450
00:24:31,867 --> 00:24:33,900
<i>What are you doing in
my girlfriend's house?</i>

451
00:24:34,033 --> 00:24:34,567
<i> You idiot!</i>

452
00:24:34,700 --> 00:24:35,300
<i> Don't try to fool me!</i>

453
00:24:35,433 --> 00:24:36,533
<i> You're a thief!</i>

454
00:24:36,667 --> 00:24:39,433
You're the one who
broke into the house!

455
00:24:39,567 --> 00:24:40,900
No wonder you look familiar!

456
00:24:41,033 --> 00:24:42,633
I don't know what
you're talking about!

457
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:43,867
I'm a cop!

458
00:24:44,167 --> 00:24:45,700
My god, Hazel!

459
00:24:45,833 --> 00:24:47,433
Is this one of your people?

460
00:24:47,567 --> 00:24:49,400
You actually ordered us
to be robbed?

461
00:24:49,633 --> 00:24:50,367
Yeah, he's the one!

462
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:52,067
He's the one Jeffrey caught!

463
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:54,167
Hey! What are you saying?

464
00:24:54,300 --> 00:24:55,467
He's a cop!

465
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:56,700
He's a cop!

466
00:24:56,833 --> 00:24:59,633
I brought him as backup to get
my husband and child out!

467
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:02,267
Didang, call security.

468
00:25:02,633 --> 00:25:04,333
- Let go of me!
- Wait, why are you filming?

469
00:25:04,467 --> 00:25:06,000
- I told you, I'm a cop.
- Stop that right now!

470
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:07,000
Why?

471
00:25:07,133 --> 00:25:08,800
Are you scared?

472
00:25:08,933 --> 00:25:10,033
That the whole world
will find out

473
00:25:10,167 --> 00:25:11,867
you're hiding my husband
and child?

474
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:14,133
Pretending to be all quiet,

475
00:25:14,567 --> 00:25:16,200
pretending to be innocent,
clueless.

476
00:25:16,333 --> 00:25:17,600
But all this time,

477
00:25:17,733 --> 00:25:19,700
my husband and child
were right here in your house!

478
00:25:19,833 --> 00:25:21,800
Oh, come on! I'm the one
hiding my dad!

479
00:25:21,933 --> 00:25:23,667
So don't drag mom into this!

480
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:24,767
There!

481
00:25:24,900 --> 00:25:26,400
So I was right all along.

482
00:25:26,533 --> 00:25:28,167
Manuel and Jessica
really are here.

483
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:29,767
That sounds like
your mom's voice.

484
00:25:29,900 --> 00:25:32,100
Dear, please help me.

485
00:25:32,233 --> 00:25:34,367
But, Dad, Aunt Felma said
we shouldn't go out

486
00:25:34,500 --> 00:25:35,567
when mommy arrives.

487
00:25:35,733 --> 00:25:37,467
Come on, listen to me, dear.
Come here now.

488
00:25:37,600 --> 00:25:38,633
You're losing your mind!

489
00:25:40,067 --> 00:25:41,167
You're taking what's mine!

490
00:25:41,300 --> 00:25:41,900
My husband and child!

491
00:25:42,033 --> 00:25:43,600
Taken by someone like you!

492
00:25:43,733 --> 00:25:45,367
- There! Here!
- Stop it!

493
00:25:45,500 --> 00:25:46,867
- She kidnapped
- Stop it!

494
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:48,467
- my husband and child!
- Stop it!

495
00:25:49,833 --> 00:25:52,933
I told you, don't hurt my child!

496
00:25:53,067 --> 00:25:54,833
Are you going to hurt me?

497
00:25:54,967 --> 00:25:56,233
Hazel!

498
00:25:56,367 --> 00:25:57,567
Hazel, that's enough!

499
00:25:57,700 --> 00:25:59,000
Don't hurt them!

500
00:26:05,067 --> 00:26:08,133
I want to sue my husband
for kidnapping my daughter.

501
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:09,600
I want them to be
put behind bars.

502
00:26:09,733 --> 00:26:10,600
Really?

503
00:26:11,033 --> 00:26:12,033
So Andeng stayed there?

504
00:26:12,167 --> 00:26:14,533
I just called you
so you wouldn't worry.

505
00:26:14,667 --> 00:26:16,300
Let's go see Andrea,
your sister.
